  "prompt": "How much is a kidney transplant in the USA?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2021, the cost of a kidney transplant in the United States can vary widely but typically falls between $250,000 and $500,000. This estimate generally includes costs related to the surgery, hospital stay, medications, and follow-up care. \n\nHowever, costs can differ based on factors such as the healthcare facility, the patient's insurance coverage, geographic location, and any complications that may arise. Additionally, expenses may not be limited to just the transplant itself, as ongoing care, including immunosuppressive medications to prevent organ rejection, can also be considerable.\n\nFor the most accurate and current information, it's advisable to consult healthcare providers, insurance companies, or healthcare financial counselors.",
